31 Kerbogha, called also Corbaya‚ Corbayath, Curbanaan, and Corbahan, was Atabek, or Prince, of Mosul. He was a follower of Barkiarok‚ one of the sons of the Sultan Melikschah, who was disputing the sultanate with his brothers. The expedition of Kerbogha represents the rather feeble effort of the Caliph of Bagdad to unite the quarreling brothers against the Chris- tian invaders,
